                    </div>
                    <span>Ray Kurtzweil mentions some impressive things in this, but for every viable argument he puts forth, he spouts off two bits of obvious nonsense. If you read this book, I suggest you skip the first two or three chapters--after that, he stops making so many predicitons and keeps himself a little more grounded. 
<br />
<br />On the whole, entertaining but not edifying.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">great for 1999</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
                      <span>5</span>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Helpful: </span>
